WEBVTT

00:00.119 --> 00:01.404
- Previously
on "The Rookie"...

00:01.404 --> 00:04.204
- I can't just go back
to the way things were.

00:04.204 --> 00:06.240
- Are you breaking up with me?
- I'm sorry.

00:06.240 --> 00:08.709
- Blair London,
rookie police psychiatrist.

00:08.709 --> 00:10.043
She had leverage on Mad Dog.

00:10.043 --> 00:12.346
- She's blackmailed one cop,
there may be more.

00:12.346 --> 00:15.916
- Someone is trying to kill me,
and I need to know who.

00:15.916 --> 00:17.784
- I want you to help me
break out of prison.

00:17.784 --> 00:18.752
- Jason.

00:18.752 --> 00:19.753
- Who are you?
- Her boyfriend.

00:19.753 --> 00:21.288
And you are?
- Her husband.

00:21.288 --> 00:24.324
[gunshot]
- Nolan!

00:24.324 --> 00:25.726
- What's wrong?

00:25.726 --> 00:27.127
- Oscar and Jason
just escaped from prison.

00:32.900 --> 00:35.469
[plane roaring overhead]

00:40.374 --> 00:42.776
- SWAT says ten-minute warning.
We should get down there.

00:42.776 --> 00:44.444
Unless you want to
sit this one out.

00:44.444 --> 00:45.979
- No, I'm good.

00:45.979 --> 00:48.615
- With all due respect, sir,
nobody would fault you.

00:48.615 --> 00:50.784
You're one day back
from being wounded in the line.

00:50.784 --> 00:53.186
- Got to get right back
on that horse, Officer Juarez.

00:53.186 --> 00:54.955
Especially a man
of a certain age.

00:54.955 --> 00:57.024
- I would guess getting shot
in your hindquarters

00:57.024 --> 00:59.393
might make horse riding
problematic, sir.

00:59.393 --> 01:01.061
- You making fun,
Officer Juarez?

01:01.061 --> 01:02.462
- Not at all, sir.
- Good.

01:02.462 --> 01:04.164
Still got three months left
in your training.

01:04.164 --> 01:05.832
It's imperative you
stay on my good side.

01:07.868 --> 01:10.137
- You really think
Jason is in the target house?

01:10.137 --> 01:11.505
- Damn sure hope so.

01:11.505 --> 01:13.840
CI says that he's been hanging
with the occupants.

01:13.840 --> 01:16.243
Bailey's deployment with
the National Guard ends soon.

01:16.243 --> 01:17.711
It's all I could do
to get her to extend

01:17.711 --> 01:19.846
so she stays safe
outside the country.

01:19.846 --> 01:21.248
[suspenseful music]

01:21.248 --> 01:24.418
[Nolan takes deep breath]

01:24.418 --> 01:26.720
All right, let's get this done.

01:26.720 --> 01:27.721
[plane roaring overhead]

01:27.721 --> 01:29.723
♪ ♪

01:29.723 --> 01:31.625
- Overwatch counts
four occupants,

01:31.625 --> 01:32.793
but there could be more.

01:32.793 --> 01:34.328
Three male, one female.

01:34.328 --> 01:36.029
Photos are being sent
to your devices.

01:36.029 --> 01:37.798
- These are violent criminals
all looking at three strikes,

01:37.798 --> 01:39.199
so they're not gonna
go down easy.

01:39.199 --> 01:40.667
- We won't have air support

01:40.667 --> 01:42.269
given our proximity
to the airport

01:42.269 --> 01:44.104
and Overwatch's field of view
is imperfect,

01:44.104 --> 01:46.873
so let's make sure
we communicate out there.

01:46.873 --> 01:48.008
- Any questions?

01:48.008 --> 01:50.077
- Yeah, Sergeant.
Um, sorry. Lieutenant.

01:50.077 --> 01:51.244
- [chuckling] All good.

01:51.244 --> 01:52.412
I'm still getting used to it
myself.

01:52.412 --> 01:53.847
- Why don't we have
a fixed perimeter?

01:53.847 --> 01:55.315
- Our targets have known
associates in the neighborhood.

01:55.315 --> 01:56.683
We don't want them
raising the alarm,

01:56.683 --> 01:58.852
so our perimeter will roll in
at the last minute.

01:58.852 --> 02:00.354
We good?
Now let's get ready.

02:00.354 --> 02:05.392
♪ ♪

02:05.392 --> 02:08.261
Hey.

02:08.261 --> 02:09.363
You up for this?

02:09.363 --> 02:11.131
No shame being
in the second wave.

02:11.131 --> 02:12.933
- No, I'm good to go, sir.

02:12.933 --> 02:14.234
- OK.
Mount up.

02:14.234 --> 02:15.669
♪ ♪

02:15.669 --> 02:18.638
[gunfire on TV]

02:18.638 --> 02:20.540
♪ ♪

02:20.540 --> 02:21.742
- Is our boy up yet?

02:21.742 --> 02:23.043
- Haven't seen him.

02:23.043 --> 02:25.112
- He was hitting it pretty hard
last night.

02:25.112 --> 02:26.113
[person screams]

02:26.113 --> 02:29.016
[tense music]

02:29.016 --> 02:36.056
♪ ♪

02:43.897 --> 02:44.898
Cops!

02:44.898 --> 02:48.068
[intense dramatic music]

02:48.068 --> 02:54.975
♪ ♪

03:00.781 --> 03:01.782
- Go, go, go.

03:01.782 --> 03:03.517
[gunfire]

03:03.517 --> 03:05.419
- Officers taking fire
in the primary entrance.

03:05.419 --> 03:06.653
One officer down.

03:06.653 --> 03:08.288
We are evacuating
through the A side.

03:08.288 --> 03:09.523
Everyone else hold.

03:09.523 --> 03:12.025
Do not advance
through the primary doorway.

03:12.025 --> 03:19.032
♪ ♪

03:20.967 --> 03:21.968
- Over here!

03:21.968 --> 03:28.141
♪ ♪

03:28.141 --> 03:29.643
- Get in.

03:29.643 --> 03:36.683
♪ ♪

03:38.985 --> 03:41.455
[gunfire inside house]

03:41.455 --> 03:42.989
[tense music]

03:42.989 --> 03:44.958
- Runner!
I'm going in. Cover me.

03:44.958 --> 03:45.959
- Gotcha.

03:45.959 --> 03:47.260
♪ ♪

03:47.260 --> 03:48.829
[plane roaring overhead]

03:48.829 --> 03:55.836
♪ ♪

03:56.603 --> 03:58.038
Ah.

03:58.038 --> 04:01.141
[nearby gunfire]

04:09.549 --> 04:11.218
- Control,
Bradford and Chen making entry

04:11.218 --> 04:13.220
bathroom window, east side.

04:13.220 --> 04:14.921
Be advised.
Potential blue-on-blue.

04:14.921 --> 04:17.557
Repeat.
Blue-on-blue.

04:17.557 --> 04:19.826
Ready?
- Yep.

04:19.826 --> 04:22.796
[tense music]

04:22.796 --> 04:24.931
♪ ♪

04:24.931 --> 04:26.433
- 7-Adam-15.
Foot pursuit.

04:26.433 --> 04:28.668
Female raid suspect
heading south towards Bellanca.

04:28.668 --> 04:31.705
♪ ♪

04:31.705 --> 04:33.206
[car horn honks]
No, no, no, no, no!

04:33.206 --> 04:35.876
I need you to back up!
Back up!

04:35.876 --> 04:37.077
- Ma'am, police.

04:37.077 --> 04:39.513
I need to commandeer your ride.
Thanks.

04:39.513 --> 04:41.181
- ♪ Don't be acting
like you know me ♪

04:41.181 --> 04:42.582
♪ Bang in the sub ♪

04:42.582 --> 04:43.583
♪ They keep blowing
like a dope fiend ♪

04:43.583 --> 04:44.684
- Sir!
Damn it.

04:44.684 --> 04:46.186
I lost sight of her.

04:46.186 --> 04:47.521
♪ ♪

04:47.521 --> 04:49.156
- ♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

04:49.156 --> 04:51.024
- [grunts]

04:51.024 --> 04:52.392
♪ ♪

04:52.392 --> 04:53.693
- Control, this is Chen.

04:53.693 --> 04:55.629
We have one suspect in custody,
east bathroom.

04:55.629 --> 04:56.863
We're advancing
through the house.

04:56.863 --> 04:58.598
Outside officers be advised,

04:58.598 --> 05:00.767
we are still downrange of fire.

05:00.767 --> 05:03.570
Blue-on-blue.
Will advise when we're clear.

05:03.570 --> 05:04.971
Yeah.

05:04.971 --> 05:08.708
♪ ♪

05:08.708 --> 05:11.244
- ♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

05:11.244 --> 05:13.914
♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

05:13.914 --> 05:16.583
♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

05:16.583 --> 05:18.652
♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

05:18.652 --> 05:20.420
♪ Making moves,
doing what I choose ♪

05:20.420 --> 05:21.721
♪ Never will I lose ♪

05:21.721 --> 05:23.223
♪ Triple gun,
I'ma get it, too ♪

05:23.223 --> 05:24.457
- Police!
Show me your hands!

05:24.457 --> 05:25.625
- ♪ Go against the crew ♪

05:25.625 --> 05:27.060
♪ This ain't nothing new ♪

05:27.060 --> 05:29.930
♪ You don't know the rules,
and you better ♪

05:29.930 --> 05:32.666
♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

05:32.666 --> 05:35.235
♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

05:35.235 --> 05:38.004
♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

05:38.004 --> 05:40.874
♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

05:40.874 --> 05:42.142
♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

05:42.142 --> 05:43.143
- On your 6:00.

05:43.143 --> 05:44.477
- Cuff him.

05:44.477 --> 05:46.413
- ♪ Now you speaking
my language ♪

05:46.413 --> 05:48.481
- I give up.

05:48.481 --> 05:50.150
- Get down!
On the floor!

05:50.150 --> 05:51.251
[handcuffs click]

05:51.251 --> 05:52.752
- Any sign of Jason?

05:52.752 --> 05:55.155
- Negative--we haven't finished
clearing the house yet.

05:55.155 --> 05:57.991
[distant sirens wailing]

06:13.773 --> 06:15.008
- Police!
Hands!

06:15.008 --> 06:16.977
Show me your hands!

06:16.977 --> 06:18.111
- [gasps]

06:18.111 --> 06:20.280
- Where's Jason?
- I don't know.

06:20.280 --> 06:22.449
- You got one shot
at telling us the truth here.

06:22.449 --> 06:24.651
- I swear, I-I don't know.
I never met him.

06:24.651 --> 06:27.587
[tense electronic music]

06:27.587 --> 06:32.425
♪ ♪

06:32.425 --> 06:34.027
[Nolan grunts]

06:34.027 --> 06:35.428
- Stay down, stay down.

06:35.428 --> 06:39.065
♪ ♪

06:39.065 --> 06:40.500
[music stops]

06:40.500 --> 06:41.701
- Hey.

06:41.701 --> 06:42.769
- Gimme that arm.

06:42.769 --> 06:44.437
Hands.
[suspect groans]

06:44.437 --> 06:45.972
- You OK?
- Yeah.

06:45.972 --> 06:47.207
- Yeah?
- I'm good.

06:47.207 --> 06:49.042
- How the hell did you get here
before me?

06:49.042 --> 06:50.977
- Work smarter, not harder.

06:50.977 --> 06:53.546
[exhales deeply]

06:53.546 --> 06:55.982
[grunts]
Come on, get up.

06:55.982 --> 06:57.651
Ow.
[groans]

06:57.651 --> 06:58.752
- Are you sure
you're all right?

06:58.752 --> 07:00.754
- Yeah, yeah.
Like I said, Code-4.

07:00.754 --> 07:03.323
7-Adam-15.
Fourth suspect in custody.

07:03.323 --> 07:04.658
Code-4.

07:04.658 --> 07:06.993
- Copy. House is secure.
All suspects in custody.

07:06.993 --> 07:08.395
No sign of Jason.

07:08.395 --> 07:11.331
- Damn it.
[groans]

07:11.331 --> 07:12.699
[groans]

07:13.967 --> 07:17.604
[bright upbeat rock music]

07:17.604 --> 07:19.005
- ♪ One, two, three, four! ♪

07:19.005 --> 07:26.046
♪ ♪

07:30.583 --> 07:32.986
- I'm just saying
it's not a great idea

07:32.986 --> 07:35.288
to show up your TO
at a workout.

07:35.288 --> 07:37.090
- A, I did no such thing.

07:37.090 --> 07:39.392
B, it's my first day
in short sleeves.

07:39.392 --> 07:41.594
I got to make sure the gun show
is popping.

07:41.594 --> 07:42.929
- [laughing] Oh, I see.

07:42.929 --> 07:45.065
So you're planning
on flaunting your superiority

07:45.065 --> 07:46.800
over the new incoming rookies?

07:46.800 --> 07:48.034
- Not at all.

07:48.034 --> 07:50.003
I plan to be
a welcoming presence

07:50.003 --> 07:52.038
as a veteran member
of the FTO program.

07:52.038 --> 07:53.239
- [laughs]

07:53.239 --> 07:54.541
- What?

07:54.541 --> 07:56.576
- A veteran member
of the FTO program.

07:56.576 --> 07:58.178
You are still a rookie.

07:58.178 --> 07:59.245
You still got to sit
in the front row

07:59.245 --> 08:00.347
with the other newbies.

08:00.347 --> 08:01.781
- Why you got to be
such a hater?

08:01.781 --> 08:02.882
- It's in the job description.

08:02.882 --> 08:04.651
♪ ♪

08:04.651 --> 08:06.486
- [sighs] I'm so nervous.

08:06.486 --> 08:07.787
You nervous?

08:07.787 --> 08:08.788
That's stupid.
You don't get--

08:08.788 --> 08:10.357
you don't get nervous.

08:10.357 --> 08:13.126
- Not getting and not showing
are two different things.

08:13.126 --> 08:14.527
Can't let them smell fear,
dude.

08:14.527 --> 08:15.795
They'll eat you alive,

08:15.795 --> 08:17.831
so you got to walk the walk
no matter what.

08:17.831 --> 08:18.998
- [chuckles softly]

08:18.998 --> 08:21.601
♪ ♪

08:21.601 --> 08:22.769
- Why aren't you ready yet,
Boot?

08:22.769 --> 08:24.170
Roll call starts in ten.

08:24.170 --> 08:26.306
- I, um--we--
I am getting ready, sir.

08:26.306 --> 08:27.307
Sergeant, sir--

08:27.307 --> 08:29.342
Sergeant, sir!

08:29.342 --> 08:30.944
- Let me make this easy
for you, Boot.

08:30.944 --> 08:33.646
Don't bother lacing up.
You don't belong here.

08:33.646 --> 08:35.648
Better to quit now than be
embarrassed out on the street.

08:35.648 --> 08:37.817
♪ ♪

08:37.817 --> 08:39.452
Something funny?
- No, sir.

08:39.452 --> 08:42.155
I got mad respect for
a real-life drill sergeant.

08:42.155 --> 08:45.492
Many aspire, but few live it,
as you so clearly do.

08:45.492 --> 08:47.293
- Morning!

08:47.293 --> 08:48.962
Are these the Academy's finest?

08:48.962 --> 08:50.363
- Negative.

08:50.363 --> 08:51.865
These two are scraped
from the bottom of the barrel.

08:51.865 --> 08:53.533
A fainting goat and a peacock.

08:53.533 --> 08:55.702
- [chuckles] Well, welcome
to the crucible, gentlemen.

08:55.702 --> 08:58.438
I look forward to learning your
names if you survive the week.

08:58.438 --> 09:02.809
♪ ♪

09:02.809 --> 09:03.977
[Seth chuckles]

09:03.977 --> 09:07.580
♪ ♪

09:07.580 --> 09:08.681
- Hey.

09:08.681 --> 09:10.350
This doesn't look fun.
- It's not.

09:10.350 --> 09:12.485
The only downside
about making lieutenant

09:12.485 --> 09:15.422
is now I'm in charge
of the patrol budget.

09:15.422 --> 09:17.524
And I have two new rookies
starting today

09:17.524 --> 09:19.759
and only one available
training officer.

09:19.759 --> 09:21.761
- Oh.
Well, what about Smitty?

09:23.163 --> 09:25.498
- Anyway,
this is why you're here.

09:25.498 --> 09:28.401
I used my new rank,
pull some strings,

09:28.401 --> 09:32.705
and got you
an interim promotion to P3.

09:32.705 --> 09:33.907
- Wow, I--

09:33.907 --> 09:35.275
That's very kind, but--

09:35.275 --> 09:37.377
- But your goal is
to work undercover.

09:37.377 --> 09:38.378
I know.

09:38.378 --> 09:39.379
This is short-term.

09:39.379 --> 09:41.381
Helping me out of a jam.

09:41.381 --> 09:43.349
Hey, I'd owe you.

09:43.349 --> 09:45.084
And this will only
strengthen your position

09:45.084 --> 09:47.020
when a detective slot opens up.

09:47.020 --> 09:48.221
- Understood.

09:48.221 --> 09:50.290
I-I'm honored you asked.

09:50.290 --> 09:51.624
I won't let you down.

09:51.624 --> 09:52.625
- I know you won't.

09:52.625 --> 09:54.094
[knock at door]

09:54.094 --> 09:55.628
- Hey.

09:55.628 --> 09:56.930
Sorry to interrupt.

09:56.930 --> 09:58.631
You wanted to see me
before roll call?

09:58.631 --> 10:00.066
- Officer Chen is stepping up

10:00.066 --> 10:01.734
to train one
of our new rookies.

10:01.734 --> 10:05.338
- Good choice.
She had an excellent teacher.

10:05.338 --> 10:07.173
- Well, was it the teacher
or the student?

10:07.173 --> 10:08.641
- OK, I don't know
what this is,

10:08.641 --> 10:11.377
but I need to finish up
the paperwork before roll call.

10:11.377 --> 10:12.879
Thank you.
- Thank you, sir.

10:12.879 --> 10:13.980
- Seriously,
if you need any pointers,

10:13.980 --> 10:15.715
don't hesitate to ask.
- Thank you.

10:15.715 --> 10:17.717
But I'm very familiar
with your bag of tricks.

10:17.717 --> 10:20.887
I'll be using a more modern
approach to train my rookie.

10:20.887 --> 10:22.322
- Cut the crust
off his sandwiches,

10:22.322 --> 10:24.057
making them feel supported?

10:24.057 --> 10:26.359
- My job is to set him up
for success,

10:26.359 --> 10:27.894
not push him to failure.

10:27.894 --> 10:29.095
- Care to put money on it?

10:29.095 --> 10:32.065
- On what?
Who trains a better rookie?

10:32.065 --> 10:33.066
No, thank you.

10:33.066 --> 10:34.067
That's so--

10:35.168 --> 10:37.203
[quirky tense music]

10:37.203 --> 10:38.905
What exactly would the terms
of the bet be?

10:38.905 --> 10:40.540
- Whose rookie's best-trained
after a month.

10:40.540 --> 10:42.242
Most successes,
fewest infractions,

10:42.242 --> 10:44.077
each day's reports
independently verified.

10:44.077 --> 10:45.745
But I understand
if you want no part of it.

10:45.745 --> 10:48.748
I mean, I'm a veteran,
you're a rookie TO.

10:48.748 --> 10:51.084
It's not really a fair contest.

10:51.084 --> 10:52.685
- Bring it on.

10:52.685 --> 10:55.021
♪ ♪

10:55.021 --> 10:56.789
[indistinct chatter]

10:56.789 --> 10:58.558
Hey, over here.

10:58.558 --> 11:00.226
Celina Juarez.

11:00.226 --> 11:03.696
Rookies sit in the front row
and only speak when spoken to.

11:03.696 --> 11:04.864
I've been here ten months

11:04.864 --> 11:06.099
and I'm happy
to show you the ropes.

11:06.099 --> 11:07.634
- OK. That's awesome.
Thank you.

11:07.634 --> 11:10.436
- Appreciate it, but I'm good.
I'm only technically a rookie.

11:10.436 --> 11:13.306
Got two years of policing
under my belt back in Texas.

11:13.306 --> 11:14.641
- Oh.

11:14.641 --> 11:17.143
Well, that's--
that's--that's amazing.

11:18.578 --> 11:21.414
- Good morning
and congratulations.

11:21.414 --> 11:23.616
Welcome to the TO team.
- Thank you.

11:23.616 --> 11:24.817
- So which one of you
gets the ringer?

11:24.817 --> 11:26.219
- What? Ringer?

11:26.219 --> 11:29.889
- Yeah, the tall guy
is from Texas PD.

11:29.889 --> 11:31.257
Tim and I met him
in the locker room.

11:31.257 --> 11:33.459
- Wow, what kind of hustle
are you running?

11:33.459 --> 11:35.628
- There's no hustle
and he's no ringer.

11:35.628 --> 11:37.931
Cops who transfer from other
states have to be untrained

11:37.931 --> 11:39.766
and retrained
from all their bad habits.

11:39.766 --> 11:41.834
Honestly, I'm praying
Grey gives me the virgin.

11:41.834 --> 11:43.336
- All right.

11:43.336 --> 11:45.772
Good morning.
Let's get started.

11:45.772 --> 11:46.940
Detective.

11:46.940 --> 11:48.908
- Following up
on yesterday's raid,

11:48.908 --> 11:50.510
despite our winning
personalities

11:50.510 --> 11:52.779
and fearsome
interrogation methods,

11:52.779 --> 11:55.181
Detective Lopez and I
were unsuccessful

11:55.181 --> 11:57.450
in gaining any further insight
into the whereabouts

11:57.450 --> 11:59.686
of Jason Wyler
and Oscar Hutchinson,

11:59.686 --> 12:02.689
which means two
of the most dangerous men

12:02.689 --> 12:06.025
we have ever arrested
are still at large.

12:06.025 --> 12:08.328
Now, luckily,
the FBI and the U.S. Marshals

12:08.328 --> 12:11.064
are both fully engaged
in the hunt.

12:11.064 --> 12:12.865
- Given our continued fallout

12:12.865 --> 12:16.035
from the mess Monica
and Blair London created,

12:16.035 --> 12:20.139
ADA Wesley Evers has
been assigned here temporarily

12:20.139 --> 12:21.374
to make sure
we're flying right.

12:21.374 --> 12:22.809
[scattered groaning]
- Good morning.

12:22.809 --> 12:24.711
I understand your reactions,
but it is vital

12:24.711 --> 12:26.145
that law enforcement
show the public

12:26.145 --> 12:28.381
that we are taking this
corruption scandal seriously.

12:28.381 --> 12:29.882
So while I'm not here
to judge you,

12:29.882 --> 12:31.985
I do have a mandate
from the DA's office

12:31.985 --> 12:35.355
to review arrest reports
and ensure their completeness

12:35.355 --> 12:36.889
and viability.

12:36.889 --> 12:38.324
- Is that it?
- That's it.

12:38.324 --> 12:39.959
- Thank you, Wesley.

12:39.959 --> 12:41.728
And if that wasn't enough,

12:41.728 --> 12:44.564
we have two new rookies
starting today.

12:44.564 --> 12:48.167
Stand, state your name
and your badge numbers.

12:48.167 --> 12:50.303
- Hi, I'm--I'm Seth Ridley.

12:50.303 --> 12:52.972
Badge number 6514--

12:52.972 --> 12:54.974
651407.

12:54.974 --> 12:56.042
- Howdy.

12:56.042 --> 12:59.512
Miles Penn,
badge number 653013.

12:59.512 --> 13:01.581
Two-year veteran
of the Sugarland, Texas

13:01.581 --> 13:02.949
police department.

13:02.949 --> 13:05.618
I've known I was destined
for greatness my whole life.

13:05.618 --> 13:07.220
But I wasn't gonna find it
in a small town,

13:07.220 --> 13:08.888
so I came to Hollywood.

13:08.888 --> 13:11.691
- Officer Penn.

13:11.691 --> 13:13.760
Did I ask
for an editorial comment?

13:13.760 --> 13:15.228
- No, sir.
That was free of charge.

13:15.228 --> 13:16.729
- Well, thank you.

13:16.729 --> 13:18.698
Keep your comments
to yourself, son.

13:18.698 --> 13:21.834
Or you'll be finding greatness
elsewhere.

13:21.834 --> 13:23.169
Am I clear?

13:23.169 --> 13:24.437
- Yes, sir.

13:24.437 --> 13:26.005
- Now, you both
earned the right to be here,

13:26.005 --> 13:29.075
but you have to prove yourself
to stay.

13:29.075 --> 13:30.843
Understood?
both: Yes, sir.

13:30.843 --> 13:34.447
- Good. Officer Penn, you're
assigned to Sergeant Bradford.

13:34.447 --> 13:36.549
Officer Ridley, you'll be
riding with Officer Chen.

13:36.549 --> 13:39.786
That's it.
Be safe out there.

13:40.687 --> 13:43.122
- Just as I expected.
You got the ringer.

13:44.590 --> 13:45.892
- Hi.
- Hey.

13:45.892 --> 13:47.093
- Hi. This is gonna be
a pleasure, Officer Chen.

13:47.093 --> 13:48.628
- Nice to meet you.
Let's save all that

13:48.628 --> 13:49.996
until you get the war bags and
we set up our shop, all right?

13:49.996 --> 13:51.264
- All right. Yes, ma'am.
- All right.

13:52.165 --> 13:54.300
- Is it too late
to ask for a TO swap?

13:54.300 --> 13:56.035
- Get your eyes
off Officer Chen, Texas.

13:56.035 --> 13:57.470
You're not fit to breathe
the same air.

13:57.470 --> 13:58.604
Go get us set up.

13:58.604 --> 13:59.906
After all the peacocking
you've displayed,

13:59.906 --> 14:01.307
I'm expecting perfection.

14:01.307 --> 14:02.975
I'll be grading you
on a serious curve.

14:02.975 --> 14:06.713
[quirky music]

14:06.713 --> 14:07.880
What?
- Oh, nothing.

14:07.880 --> 14:10.316
I'm just liking my chances
right now.

14:10.316 --> 14:12.051
♪ ♪

14:12.051 --> 14:13.219
- [sighs softly]

14:13.219 --> 14:14.253
- I heard you got booed
in roll call.

14:14.253 --> 14:15.254
Who am I hurting?

14:15.254 --> 14:16.422
- That's fine.
I can take it.

14:16.422 --> 14:17.824
And having my wife
beat up the people

14:17.824 --> 14:19.325
that are mean to me
isn't gonna win me any fans.

14:19.325 --> 14:20.460
- I'm just saying,
I'll cut a bitch.

14:20.460 --> 14:22.261
- [laughs]

14:22.261 --> 14:24.330
- Nice of Metro to let you
use the liaison office.

14:24.330 --> 14:25.765
- Yeah, I need the privacy.

14:25.765 --> 14:27.800
I still need to finish
reviewing the final recordings

14:27.800 --> 14:29.502
of Blair London's
therapy sessions.

14:29.502 --> 14:30.503
- So creepy.

14:30.503 --> 14:31.938
- Yeah, tell me about it.

14:31.938 --> 14:33.940
All I feel is dirty listening
to everybody's secrets.

14:33.940 --> 14:35.341
Especially when
most are only guilty

14:35.341 --> 14:37.009
of being humans
in emotional distress.

14:38.511 --> 14:39.946
Hey.

14:39.946 --> 14:41.247
Any news on Monica?

14:41.247 --> 14:43.649
- Not since she evaded Interpol
in Bolivia.

14:50.289 --> 14:52.725
- Why did you make me wait
so long to wear short sleeves?

14:52.725 --> 14:55.161
Aaron got his way earlier
in his rookie year.

14:55.161 --> 14:56.562
- You had to earn 'em.

14:56.562 --> 14:58.531
How is Aaron doing over
in North Hollywood, anyway?

14:58.531 --> 14:59.565
- He's settling in.

14:59.565 --> 15:00.700
Happy that no one
at the station

15:00.700 --> 15:02.335
knows he was a patient
of Blair's.

15:02.335 --> 15:04.504
God, this is so freeing.

15:04.504 --> 15:06.205
- And clearly distracting.

15:06.205 --> 15:07.874
Perhaps I need to reverse
the privilege.

15:07.874 --> 15:09.709
- No, no.
I-I've celebrated enough.

15:10.576 --> 15:13.346
[person screams]

15:13.346 --> 15:14.914
Whoa.
On the right.

15:14.914 --> 15:17.917
[ominous music]

15:17.917 --> 15:20.686
♪ ♪

15:20.686 --> 15:21.921
- 7-Adam-15.

15:21.921 --> 15:23.589
Possible disturbance
at El Adobe Pharmacy.

15:23.589 --> 15:24.991
Code-6 to investigate.

15:24.991 --> 15:32.031
♪ ♪

15:35.735 --> 15:36.869
- Come on, come on! Hurry!

15:36.869 --> 15:40.239
- I-I'm going as fast as I can.

15:40.239 --> 15:42.675
- 7-Adam-15.
We have a 211 armed.

15:42.675 --> 15:44.310
Send backup.

15:44.310 --> 15:45.378
Ready?

15:45.378 --> 15:48.681
♪ ♪

15:48.681 --> 15:51.050
- What are these back here?
These oxys?

15:51.050 --> 15:52.919
The big one, the big ones.

15:52.919 --> 15:55.221
Powerful stuff, come on,
powerful stuff.

15:55.221 --> 15:56.522
Hurry!

15:56.522 --> 15:57.857
Go, go, go, go!

15:57.857 --> 16:00.993
You want to get shot today?

16:02.195 --> 16:05.665
[heartbeat pounding]

16:05.665 --> 16:07.466
[muffled speech]

16:07.466 --> 16:10.470
[heartbeat pounding]

16:16.676 --> 16:19.078
[gunfire]

16:19.779 --> 16:22.281
[tense music]

16:22.281 --> 16:24.083
♪ ♪

16:24.083 --> 16:25.117
- Nolan?

16:25.117 --> 16:26.118
- I'm good!
Go!

16:26.118 --> 16:29.288
♪ ♪

16:29.288 --> 16:30.423
[gunshot]
- [screaming]

16:30.423 --> 16:32.959
- Get out of the car!
- Oh, my God!

16:32.959 --> 16:34.627
[tires squealing]

16:34.627 --> 16:35.962
- Control,
suspect just shot a victim

16:35.962 --> 16:37.897
and fled north on Kingsley
in a gray vehicle.

16:37.897 --> 16:39.465
Partial plate, Edward 2-3-9.

16:39.465 --> 16:41.801
I need an RA for
a 30-year-old male victim,

16:41.801 --> 16:42.969
single GSW to the chest.

16:42.969 --> 16:45.137
- I got it.
Just breathe.

16:45.137 --> 16:47.607
- [crying]

16:50.576 --> 16:51.911
- It's very simple.

16:51.911 --> 16:53.145
You know, my job is to
set you up for success.

16:53.145 --> 16:55.181
But things move way too fast
out on the street

16:55.181 --> 16:56.782
for me to coddle you.
Yeah?

16:56.782 --> 16:57.817
- Yeah.
I understand.

16:57.817 --> 17:00.119
Just consider me
like your sponge.

17:00.119 --> 17:02.889
I'm eager to absorb
all your knowledge.

17:02.889 --> 17:04.524
- All units, be on the lookout
for a gray vehicle.

17:04.524 --> 17:07.226
Partial license plate,
Edward 2-3-9.

17:07.226 --> 17:08.895
Suspect is white male,
black shirt, brown shirt,

17:08.895 --> 17:10.196
armed and dangerous.

17:10.196 --> 17:11.764
Shots were fired,
at least one victim.

17:11.764 --> 17:13.266
Unknown condition.

17:13.266 --> 17:15.401
- OK.

17:15.401 --> 17:18.070
Officer Ridley,
what's our follow-up?

17:18.070 --> 17:19.405
- Um--

17:19.405 --> 17:20.806
- Don't you want to know
distance of travel?

17:20.806 --> 17:21.807
The time element.

17:21.807 --> 17:23.175
- Right.
- Yeah?

17:23.175 --> 17:25.544
- Control, what is our DOT
and time element?

17:25.544 --> 17:27.680
- Six minutes ago.
South on Garmond.

17:27.680 --> 17:29.949
- Which means he's headed
away from us.

17:29.949 --> 17:32.018
- No, Garmond is north of us,

17:32.018 --> 17:33.953
which means he's coming
in our direction.

17:33.953 --> 17:36.222
- Good. And he's probably
headed towards the freeway.

17:36.222 --> 17:37.957
But the traffic's heavy
this time of morning,

17:37.957 --> 17:39.492
so if we hustle...

17:39.492 --> 17:42.028
[engine revving]
We might just catch up to him.

17:42.028 --> 17:43.562
You want to hit the lights?

17:43.562 --> 17:46.532
[siren wailing]

17:46.532 --> 17:48.334
- Do y'all have
license plate readers?

17:48.334 --> 17:50.436
I assume you do,
big city like this.

17:50.436 --> 17:52.405
- Yeah, we do.
Where you going with this?

17:52.405 --> 17:53.873
- I'm plugging in the partial.

17:53.873 --> 17:55.841
Request a real-time search
of this neighborhood.

17:58.911 --> 18:01.547
- It's OK, baby.
You're gonna be OK.

18:01.547 --> 18:03.049
Oh, my God, our daughter.
She's at school.

18:03.049 --> 18:04.050
Westside Charter.

18:04.050 --> 18:05.284
- It's OK, it's OK.

18:05.284 --> 18:06.419
Officer Juarez and I
will go pick her up

18:06.419 --> 18:07.620
and bring her to you, OK?
- Thank you.

18:07.620 --> 18:09.455
Her name is Nikki.
- Nikki. OK.

18:09.455 --> 18:10.489
[siren wails]

18:13.626 --> 18:15.127
- How bad?
- Bad.

18:15.127 --> 18:17.296
Shot in the chest,
pulse is spotty.

18:17.296 --> 18:18.965
- Something bothering you?

18:18.965 --> 18:21.334
- I just--there was a moment
inside the pharmacy

18:21.334 --> 18:25.071
where I might have had the
shot, but I didn't take it.

18:25.071 --> 18:26.672
- You think this citizen
catching a bullet outside

18:26.672 --> 18:27.707
is your fault?

18:27.707 --> 18:30.109
- No, I just couldn't tell if--

18:30.109 --> 18:31.510
if my background was clear,

18:31.510 --> 18:34.547
and then it turns out
it wasn't.

18:34.547 --> 18:36.449
- You didn't have confidence
you could make the shot?

18:36.449 --> 18:37.950
- No, sir.

18:37.950 --> 18:39.552
I'm saying I wasn't confident
I had a clean shot,

18:39.552 --> 18:41.087
and it turned out I was right.

18:41.087 --> 18:43.356
- Look, Nolan, we're in the
split-second decision business.

18:43.356 --> 18:44.857
It's no use second-guessing

18:44.857 --> 18:46.792
until we review
the body cam footage.

18:46.792 --> 18:48.227
- Yes, sir.

18:48.227 --> 18:51.263
[somber music]

18:51.263 --> 18:52.965
- You ready to go?

18:52.965 --> 18:54.233
- Yeah.

18:54.233 --> 18:57.570
We need to pick up
their daughter on the way.

18:57.570 --> 18:59.038
- Thanks, Dr. London.

18:59.038 --> 19:01.607
It feels good to finally
be able to unburden myself.

19:01.607 --> 19:02.875
I'll see you next week.

19:02.875 --> 19:05.511
- OK.
No incriminating information.

19:05.511 --> 19:07.513
Cleared.

19:07.513 --> 19:09.015
- I had that dream again, Doc.

19:09.015 --> 19:10.349
It was even hotter this time.

19:10.349 --> 19:12.051
- [chuckles]
- The things she did to me.

19:12.051 --> 19:13.786
Seriously,
this is becoming a problem.

19:13.786 --> 19:15.888
I mean, how am I supposed
to work next to Angela Lopez

19:15.888 --> 19:17.823
when all I can think about
is how much I want to--

19:17.823 --> 19:20.826
[quirky tense music]

19:20.826 --> 19:25.931
♪ ♪

19:25.931 --> 19:28.601
- Well, I think it's best
if we let your mom explain.

19:28.601 --> 19:31.771
- But what kind of accident?

19:31.771 --> 19:35.608
Is my dad gonna be OK?

19:35.608 --> 19:36.642
- We hope so.

19:36.642 --> 19:38.511
He has the very best doctors,

19:38.511 --> 19:40.446
and we're going to be at the
hospital in just a few minutes.

19:40.446 --> 19:42.081
All right?

19:42.081 --> 19:43.416
- OK.

19:43.416 --> 19:45.551
- All units,
211 suspect plates recorded

19:45.551 --> 19:48.921
heading west, 2100 block
of Lincoln ten minutes ago,

19:48.921 --> 19:51.490
but the vehicle did not pass
through the next intersection.

19:51.490 --> 19:52.858
- That's just
around the corner.

19:52.858 --> 19:53.993
There's an alley on Lincoln.

19:53.993 --> 19:56.495
Maybe he ditched the car
down there.

19:58.664 --> 20:00.700
Oh, my God.
There it is.

20:00.700 --> 20:02.368
- OK, focus, Officer Ridley.

20:02.368 --> 20:04.103
Do I park here
or pull in closer?

20:04.103 --> 20:05.805
- We, uh, we park here.

20:05.805 --> 20:07.106
- Why?

20:07.106 --> 20:08.474
- Because we can't see
if the suspect

20:08.474 --> 20:09.809
is in the vehicle or not,

20:09.809 --> 20:11.944
so it's safer to approach
on foot.

20:11.944 --> 20:13.546
- Correct.

20:14.346 --> 20:17.116
7-Adam-19, I have eyes
on the suspect vehicle.

20:17.116 --> 20:19.552
West side of the alley,
2100 block of Lincoln.

20:19.552 --> 20:22.054
Show us Code-6 to investigate.
Send backup.

20:22.054 --> 20:24.523
- Copy that, 7-Adam-19.
Be careful.

20:27.126 --> 20:30.096
- All right.
Tell me how we approach.

20:30.096 --> 20:32.198
- We have our weapons drawn,
we approach with caution,

20:32.198 --> 20:33.599
we try to call out the driver.

20:33.599 --> 20:34.834
If he does not respond,

20:34.834 --> 20:36.001
then we can
get a little bit closer.

20:36.001 --> 20:38.104
Always make sure we have
an exit route available.

20:38.104 --> 20:40.306
And we'll check the trunk
on the way up.

20:40.306 --> 20:41.974
- It's an SUV.
There is no trunk.

20:41.974 --> 20:43.976
Don't just parrot
academy training, all right?

20:43.976 --> 20:44.977
This is the real world.

20:44.977 --> 20:45.978
- Right.
Yes, ma'am.

20:45.978 --> 20:46.979
- All right.

20:46.979 --> 20:48.848
[tense music]

20:48.848 --> 20:51.117
- Control, can we make sure
that nobody comes northbound

20:51.117 --> 20:52.685
to this alley
in case there's fire?

20:52.685 --> 20:54.086
- Copy that, 7-Adam-19.

20:54.086 --> 20:56.255
- That's a good call.

20:56.255 --> 20:58.324
Driver!
This is the police!

20:58.324 --> 21:02.695
Roll down your window
and show me your hands!

21:02.695 --> 21:04.764
♪ ♪

21:04.764 --> 21:06.132
Show me your hands!

21:06.132 --> 21:07.933
Do it now!

21:07.933 --> 21:09.335
Watch your--watch your muzzle.

21:09.335 --> 21:10.703
- Sorry, sorry.

21:10.703 --> 21:12.772
- Go this way.
- OK.

21:12.772 --> 21:14.173
♪ ♪

21:14.173 --> 21:15.574
- I see the suspect.

21:15.574 --> 21:18.577
Show me your hands!

21:18.577 --> 21:19.745
- He looks dead.

21:19.745 --> 21:21.180
- We can't know for sure.

21:21.180 --> 21:22.748
Come this side.

21:22.748 --> 21:24.083
I'm gonna open the door.

21:24.083 --> 21:25.384
You grab his shoulders,
pull them out on three.

21:25.384 --> 21:26.919
OK?
- OK.

21:26.919 --> 21:28.053
♪ ♪

21:28.053 --> 21:29.889
- One, two.

21:29.889 --> 21:32.858
♪ ♪

21:34.927 --> 21:37.730
[suspect breathing]

21:37.730 --> 21:39.565
[Seth gagging]
- Hey, do not get sick.

21:39.565 --> 21:40.566
- [gagging] OK.

21:40.566 --> 21:41.667
- Don't puke on him.

21:41.667 --> 21:44.403
[Seth retching]
No.

21:44.403 --> 21:45.671
Damn it.

21:45.671 --> 21:48.007
Ridley, you just
contaminated the crime scene.

21:48.007 --> 21:49.542
- Sorry.

21:49.542 --> 21:52.344
- 7-Adam-19,
211 suspect in custody.

21:52.344 --> 21:54.880
We need RA for possible OD.

21:54.880 --> 21:55.981
- Must have been jonesing
for a fix

21:55.981 --> 21:57.483
when he robbed the pharmacy.

21:57.483 --> 22:00.152
Pulled over to dope up as soon
as he thought it was safe.

22:00.152 --> 22:03.022
On the bright side, taxpayers
save millions if he kicks it.

22:03.022 --> 22:05.324
- We never root for a suspect
to die, Officer Penn.

22:05.324 --> 22:06.659
- Yeah, totally.

22:06.659 --> 22:09.495
I-I'm just saying--
[tries squealing]

22:09.495 --> 22:11.197
- Finally, a little action
of our own.

22:11.197 --> 22:13.299
[siren wailing]

22:13.299 --> 22:14.934
Reported stolen
early this morning.

22:14.934 --> 22:17.102
Pull up close
and I'll shoot out the tires.

22:17.102 --> 22:18.137
I'm kidding, man.

22:18.137 --> 22:19.572
- [sighs]

22:19.572 --> 22:21.607
[engine revving]

22:30.850 --> 22:32.184
- Ooh, that hurt.

22:32.184 --> 22:33.919
[siren wailing]

22:33.919 --> 22:36.222
- OK, what--

22:36.222 --> 22:37.456
- Police!
Show me your hands!

22:37.456 --> 22:39.391
Show me your damn hands!

22:39.391 --> 22:41.594
Ah, he's running!

22:41.594 --> 22:43.596
Get down!
Show me your hands!

22:43.596 --> 22:45.464
[tense music]

22:45.464 --> 22:47.233
- You should have waited.

22:47.233 --> 22:48.467
That was all bad, Texas.

22:48.467 --> 22:49.735
Strike one,
you jumped out the car

22:49.735 --> 22:50.870
while I was trying
to communicate.

22:50.870 --> 22:51.937
What if I was trying
to tell you

22:51.937 --> 22:53.973
I saw a gun
or a second suspect?

22:53.973 --> 22:55.975
Strike two, you ran out
in front of my field of fire,

22:55.975 --> 22:57.876
so I couldn't engage
even if I had to.

22:57.876 --> 23:00.546
And strike three, by going
to that driver's side alone,

23:00.546 --> 23:02.214
you left an escape route
out the passenger side.

23:02.214 --> 23:03.482
And don't even get me started

23:03.482 --> 23:04.683
on your little
"shoot out the tires" comment.

23:04.683 --> 23:06.318
It is now a permanent part
of this case.

23:06.318 --> 23:07.686
That may not sound
like much now,

23:07.686 --> 23:09.188
but wait till a civil liberty
attorney hears about it.

23:09.188 --> 23:10.856
Might be writing this kid
checks for years.

23:10.856 --> 23:13.859
[somber music]

23:13.859 --> 23:16.462
♪ ♪

23:23.402 --> 23:25.237
- All right, as punishment
for being a cowboy,

23:25.237 --> 23:27.072
you're checking every VIN
on that stolen vehicle

23:27.072 --> 23:28.507
to make sure it matches.

23:28.507 --> 23:30.175
- That'll take hours, Sarge.

23:30.175 --> 23:31.744
- It's Sergeant Bradford,
not Sarge.

23:31.744 --> 23:33.045
You're way too eager
to get in trouble,

23:33.045 --> 23:34.213
so I'm slowing you down.

23:35.047 --> 23:36.715
[alarm blaring]
Back out.

23:36.715 --> 23:38.284
- Wait. Why?
What is that alarm for?

23:38.284 --> 23:39.618
- Back out!

23:39.618 --> 23:40.853
Every department garage
has a Geiger counter.

23:40.853 --> 23:43.656
This car we brought in
is radioactive.

23:43.656 --> 23:45.224
[alarm blaring]

23:45.224 --> 23:47.726
- 12 hours ago, a suitcase nuke
arrived on a Naval cargo ship

23:47.726 --> 23:48.861
from Eastern Europe.

23:48.861 --> 23:50.195
It's a Cold War relic
from Ukraine

23:50.195 --> 23:52.031
that got turned over
for demolition.

23:52.031 --> 23:54.166
A secure convoy was meant
to take it to Oklahoma

23:54.166 --> 23:55.868
to be decommissioned,
but the nuke went missing

23:55.868 --> 23:57.536
at the port
sometime before dawn.

23:57.536 --> 23:58.804
- How the hell does
that happen?

23:58.804 --> 23:59.938
- That's what we've
been desperately trying

23:59.938 --> 24:01.340
to figure out,
along with who took it

24:01.340 --> 24:02.908
and what the hell they're
planning on doing with it.

24:02.908 --> 24:04.743
- And you didn't think
to inform the LAPD?

24:04.743 --> 24:06.378
- There's been a lot of
pressure to keep this quiet,

24:06.378 --> 24:07.379
not to panic people.

24:07.379 --> 24:08.647
I argued against it,

24:08.647 --> 24:10.449
but the decision was made
up the food chain.

24:10.449 --> 24:11.917
[tense music]

24:11.917 --> 24:12.952
- [knocks on window]
You're with us.

24:12.952 --> 24:15.721
- Go study your Rook Book.

24:15.721 --> 24:17.389
- Close that.

24:17.389 --> 24:18.958
♪ ♪

24:18.958 --> 24:21.427
A battlefield nuke was stolen
from the port this morning.

24:21.427 --> 24:23.495
- And the OG backpack
runs about 80 pounds,

24:23.495 --> 24:25.097
making it highly mobile.

24:25.097 --> 24:26.932
- What do you know about
the stolen car's owner?

24:26.932 --> 24:29.101
- Paul Scoville, 31,
rent-a-cop at the port.

24:29.101 --> 24:30.402
Recently divorced.

24:30.402 --> 24:31.737
I assume money problems,

24:31.737 --> 24:33.305
but I can't confirm
till I pull his financials.

24:33.305 --> 24:34.807
- Any idea where he is now?

24:34.807 --> 24:37.042
- No. Called his house,
his cell, haven't heard back.

24:37.042 --> 24:38.777
But I just found out
he's a person of interest

24:38.777 --> 24:40.045
five seconds ago.

24:40.045 --> 24:41.580
- I'll have the office
work on the warrants.

24:41.580 --> 24:43.449
- Known associates, too?
- Oh, absolutely.

24:43.449 --> 24:45.050
We are gonna piggyback
the whole menu on this.

24:45.050 --> 24:47.286
Home, phone, storage lockers,
PO boxes,

24:47.286 --> 24:49.121
and the same
for all known associates.

24:49.121 --> 24:51.357
Anyone we can establish
a clear nexus with.

24:51.357 --> 24:52.524
I'll mobilize HRT.

24:52.524 --> 24:53.759
Can you get Metro and SWAT
up to speed?

24:53.759 --> 24:55.027
- Of course.
- Good.

24:55.027 --> 24:56.562
We're gonna need
to get ready and gear up,

24:56.562 --> 24:57.796
because when it
is time to move,

24:57.796 --> 24:59.231
we are gonna need to move fast.

24:59.231 --> 25:01.500
- Copy.

25:01.500 --> 25:04.503
[distant sirens wailing]

25:06.238 --> 25:07.573
- Hey.

25:07.573 --> 25:09.341
They officially
called time of death at 1329.

25:09.341 --> 25:10.342
- Right.

25:10.342 --> 25:11.677
- Write that down.

25:11.677 --> 25:12.911
And they still have
to do an autopsy,

25:12.911 --> 25:15.114
but it seems pretty clear
it was an overdose, so--

25:15.114 --> 25:16.482
- Listen, about earlier.

25:16.482 --> 25:18.117
- No, look, I get it.

25:18.117 --> 25:19.251
It's your first dead body.

25:19.251 --> 25:20.719
All those fluids,
it got to you.

25:20.719 --> 25:23.122
But we have to protect
the scene.

25:23.122 --> 25:24.957
- Yeah, no, I--I--

25:24.957 --> 25:26.058
yes, we got
to protect the scene,

25:26.058 --> 25:27.059
but it's not that simple.

25:27.059 --> 25:28.193
I--

25:28.193 --> 25:30.129
this is not my first OD.

25:30.129 --> 25:34.133
I had this girlfriend back
in junior year of high school,

25:34.133 --> 25:36.301
and I found her after prom

25:36.301 --> 25:38.437
in a bathroom
at Rory Hatcher's house.

25:38.437 --> 25:40.639
And, um...

25:40.639 --> 25:42.408
she had her eyes rolled back,
you know,

25:42.408 --> 25:44.676
and--
[sighs]

25:44.676 --> 25:46.345
She wasn't breathing,
so I tried to give her CPR,

25:46.345 --> 25:47.913
but--[sighs]

25:47.913 --> 25:50.015
I couldn't get the taste
of her sick out of her mouth

25:50.015 --> 25:52.317
for like two days.

25:52.317 --> 25:55.154
And I can still taste it
if I, um--

25:55.154 --> 25:56.955
[somber music]

25:56.955 --> 25:58.323
I--[clears throat]

25:58.323 --> 26:00.826
I wasn't being a delicate
flower out there today, OK?

26:00.826 --> 26:02.094
It all just came rushing back.

26:02.094 --> 26:03.695
And I promise it's not
gonna happen again.

26:03.695 --> 26:05.564
- Seth, that's awful.

26:05.564 --> 26:07.232
I'm sorry that happened to you.

26:07.232 --> 26:10.235
But in this job, we have
to separate from the personal.

26:10.235 --> 26:11.770
It's the hardest thing
we have to do.

26:11.770 --> 26:15.541
Because if we lose control,
bad things happen, right?

26:15.541 --> 26:17.076
- Understood.

26:18.777 --> 26:20.379
- Right over here.

26:23.782 --> 26:25.651
Any news?

26:25.651 --> 26:28.187
- Husband died on the table
a few minutes ago.

26:28.187 --> 26:29.688
She doesn't know yet.

26:29.688 --> 26:32.057
- Man, that's rough.
Why haven't they told her?

26:32.057 --> 26:33.358
- We asked them to wait a beat.

26:33.358 --> 26:34.893
We need to take a statement,

26:34.893 --> 26:37.429
and she'll be in no condition
to give us one when she knows.

26:39.465 --> 26:41.834
- I mean, it just seems wrong,
you know,

26:41.834 --> 26:43.135
to keep the news from her.

26:43.135 --> 26:44.570
- Yeah, and waiting
another ten minutes

26:44.570 --> 26:46.171
isn't gonna make it any worse.

26:46.171 --> 26:47.673
[phone ringing]

26:47.673 --> 26:49.575
It's Grey.
Yes, sir.

26:49.575 --> 26:50.976
- I'm here with
Special Agent Garza.

26:50.976 --> 26:53.479
We have a situation
that's not for broadcast.

26:53.479 --> 26:55.180
A battlefield nuke is at large.

26:55.180 --> 26:56.682
Small yield,
but high dispersal.

26:56.682 --> 26:57.883
- We need you
and Officer Juarez

26:57.883 --> 26:59.118
to go put eyes on
a suspect's house

26:59.118 --> 27:00.819
while FBI and SWAT mobilize.

27:00.819 --> 27:01.987
Address to your box.

27:01.987 --> 27:03.722
- Yes, sirs.
On it.

27:03.722 --> 27:05.390
- What's happening?
- Nothing good.

27:05.390 --> 27:06.859
[ominous music]

27:10.929 --> 27:13.532
- [clears throat]
Detective Graham, right?

27:13.532 --> 27:15.634
- Yes, sir.

27:15.634 --> 27:18.237
You're the hall monitor
from the DA's office.

27:18.237 --> 27:19.371
- [laughs]

27:19.371 --> 27:20.906
- I'm actually thrilled
you're here.

27:20.906 --> 27:23.909
Anything you can do to improve
on patrol's paperwork

27:23.909 --> 27:25.978
is a lifesaver.

27:25.978 --> 27:29.014
- You work with my wife,
Angela Lopez.

27:29.014 --> 27:30.415
- Oh, yeah.

27:30.415 --> 27:31.617
She's amazing.
- Mm.

27:31.617 --> 27:32.818
- Sure you already know that.

27:32.818 --> 27:34.219
- Yeah, I do.

27:34.219 --> 27:36.922
- I have to admit I didn't
think you guys would last.

27:36.922 --> 27:38.757
I always thought
she'd end up with a cop.

27:38.757 --> 27:40.292
[quirky tense music]

27:40.292 --> 27:44.229
- And yet here we are,
happily married, two kids.

27:44.229 --> 27:46.698
- Well, you must be
doing something right.

27:47.966 --> 27:50.435
♪ ♪

27:53.105 --> 27:54.172
- A little more.

27:56.575 --> 27:59.011
Right there.
Perfect.

28:05.184 --> 28:06.718
- How you doing?

28:06.718 --> 28:08.954
- I'm fine.

28:08.954 --> 28:10.689
- If you want to talk
about anything--

28:10.689 --> 28:12.491
- I don't.

28:12.491 --> 28:14.660
- I'm just saying
if it was me,

28:14.660 --> 28:17.062
I'd be beating myself up,
wondering if there was

28:17.062 --> 28:18.363
anything I could have
done differently

28:18.363 --> 28:19.364
inside the pharmacy.

28:19.364 --> 28:21.500
- And I said I'm good.

28:21.500 --> 28:24.536
- Right, no.
Yeah, you did.

28:24.536 --> 28:27.639
But if I was going through
that self-doubt,

28:27.639 --> 28:31.543
what would you say to me
as my training officer?

28:31.543 --> 28:35.180
- Well, I would say that the
whole benefit of experience

28:35.180 --> 28:37.683
is to learn from each incident,

28:37.683 --> 28:40.752
both victories and mistakes.

28:40.752 --> 28:43.989
So if the situation
ever happens again,

28:43.989 --> 28:45.390
it'll be a win.

28:45.390 --> 28:48.060
- It's a brutal job
to have to learn as you go.

28:50.896 --> 28:53.232
- Contact.

28:53.232 --> 28:55.734
It appears there's been
a little falling out

28:55.734 --> 28:57.803
between nuclear thieves.

28:57.803 --> 28:59.438
- We have to intervene, right?

28:59.438 --> 29:00.939
Even though we're just meant
to observe?

29:00.939 --> 29:01.940
- Well, it depends.

29:01.940 --> 29:03.242
As harsh as it may sound,

29:03.242 --> 29:05.744
if that man is dead,
he's just evidence now.

29:05.744 --> 29:07.112
- OK, well, what if he's alive

29:07.112 --> 29:09.581
and needs help
and we don't do anything?

29:09.581 --> 29:12.784
[tense music]

29:12.784 --> 29:15.721
♪ ♪

29:15.721 --> 29:17.189
What's the plan?

29:17.189 --> 29:18.523
- Well, we can't go in there
guns blazing.

29:18.523 --> 29:20.993
We need those guys alive
in case the nuke isn't here.

29:20.993 --> 29:23.962
So stealth and surprise.

29:23.962 --> 29:26.498
What are you wearing
under that uniform?

29:27.833 --> 29:29.768
[knock at door]

29:29.768 --> 29:31.703
♪ ♪

29:31.703 --> 29:33.639
- Hello?
I need your help.

29:33.639 --> 29:34.940
Please.

29:34.940 --> 29:36.308
- What?
- I lost my dog.

29:36.308 --> 29:37.709
We were jogging.

29:37.709 --> 29:38.910
He pulled the leash
out of my hand.

29:38.910 --> 29:40.545
It's a brown labradoodle.
Have you seen him?

29:40.545 --> 29:41.880
- No.

29:41.880 --> 29:43.749
- Can I--
can I check your backyard

29:43.749 --> 29:45.617
just to make sure
he didn't get back there?

29:45.617 --> 29:47.452
- Um, no. I'm sorry.
[floorboard creaks]

29:47.452 --> 29:48.954
- Police!
Show me your hands.

29:48.954 --> 29:52.190
[sirens wailing]

29:52.190 --> 29:54.292
[tires squealing]

29:56.862 --> 29:59.665
[Geiger counter clicking]

30:01.066 --> 30:02.868
We got two in custody.
Scoville's in the tub.

30:02.868 --> 30:05.070
He's still breathing,
but he needs an ambulance ASAP.

30:06.238 --> 30:08.940
- Nothing, boss.
Mm-mm.

30:08.940 --> 30:10.909
- There are no traces
of radiation in this house,

30:10.909 --> 30:11.910
so the nuke isn't here.

30:11.910 --> 30:13.045
It never was.

30:13.045 --> 30:14.513
So we are gonna have ourselves

30:14.513 --> 30:17.182
a long, hard conversation.

30:17.182 --> 30:18.550
- You're wasting your breath.

30:18.550 --> 30:19.751
I ain't talking.

30:19.751 --> 30:21.386
- That's fine.

30:21.386 --> 30:22.888
Better you listen
for the moment anyway,

30:22.888 --> 30:24.322
because what you choose
to do next

30:24.322 --> 30:26.958
will decide the rest
of your life.

30:26.958 --> 30:31.596
- Paul Scoville is clinging
to his life at Saint Stephens.

30:31.596 --> 30:33.799
So as of this moment,

30:33.799 --> 30:37.369
there's still a path
to immunity for you.

30:37.369 --> 30:39.404
We can hang the charges
on your crew,

30:39.404 --> 30:42.140
give you a golden ticket
to a new life.

30:42.140 --> 30:46.411
But we need names
and a location for the device.

30:46.411 --> 30:47.412
- I told you--

30:47.412 --> 30:48.814
- Shut up!

30:51.516 --> 30:53.285
You have literally
five minutes to decide

30:53.285 --> 30:55.554
if you are gonna be
part of the solution

30:55.554 --> 30:58.290
or go to prison
as a domestic terrorist.

31:02.861 --> 31:04.129
- You think he'll flip
on his guys?

31:04.129 --> 31:06.732
- He has to.
There's no other option.

31:07.766 --> 31:09.234
- How's it going
with your cowboy?

31:09.234 --> 31:10.302
[quirky tense music]

31:10.302 --> 31:11.937
- Great.
How's the virgin?

31:11.937 --> 31:13.338
- Great.

31:13.338 --> 31:16.675
♪ ♪

31:16.675 --> 31:18.677
- Celina's doing great, too.
Thank you for asking.

31:19.978 --> 31:23.148
- [sighs]
Is it always this intense?

31:23.148 --> 31:24.182
- No.

31:24.182 --> 31:26.351
Well, hmm, kind of.

31:26.351 --> 31:28.120
- That's the point, though,
right?

31:28.120 --> 31:31.456
If you prove yourself here,
you know that you're the best.

31:31.456 --> 31:33.525
- I--it's not really like that.

31:33.525 --> 31:36.495
For me, I--I, um--
[clears throat]

31:36.495 --> 31:38.396
I just want to help people.

31:38.396 --> 31:39.564
- Hmm.

31:39.564 --> 31:41.333
Aries, Pisces?

31:41.333 --> 31:43.468
- Yeah.
- How did--how'd you know?

31:43.468 --> 31:45.604
- Well, it's a--it's a gift.

31:45.604 --> 31:46.972
Um--

31:50.876 --> 31:52.110
Everything OK?

31:52.110 --> 31:53.445
- What?

31:53.445 --> 31:55.614
- No, just you have
a pained look on your face.

31:55.614 --> 31:56.648
Just checking to make sure

31:56.648 --> 31:57.916
you're not having
a heart attack.

31:57.916 --> 31:59.518
- Oh, no, no, no.
No, I'm fine.

31:59.518 --> 32:00.752
I'm fine.

32:00.752 --> 32:02.687
It's just I'm an officer
of the court.

32:02.687 --> 32:04.156
I can't violate
the confidentiality

32:04.156 --> 32:05.490
that I've been entrusted with.

32:05.490 --> 32:06.825
And that's the--

32:06.825 --> 32:09.694
the cornerstone of
the legal profession, really.

32:09.694 --> 32:11.496
No matter how much you want
to unknow what you know,

32:11.496 --> 32:13.932
you can't,
it's just there, always.

32:13.932 --> 32:15.967
Every time you close your eyes.

32:15.967 --> 32:17.569
- Uh--
- Hey,

32:17.569 --> 32:18.637
they need you in interrogation.

32:18.637 --> 32:19.871
Nuclear guy's ready to talk,

32:19.871 --> 32:21.072
but they need you to sign off
on the deal.

32:21.072 --> 32:22.240
- Right.

32:22.240 --> 32:23.241
Right.

32:23.241 --> 32:26.278
[suspenseful music]

32:26.278 --> 32:28.580
- Crew leader's Marcus Leonard.

32:28.580 --> 32:31.283
He's holed up in a rental
in West LA

32:31.283 --> 32:34.753
with Evan Ardle
and LeShawn Wilkes.

32:34.753 --> 32:37.389
That's where the nuke is.

32:37.389 --> 32:40.025
We're waiting to rendezvous
with a buyer in the desert.

32:40.025 --> 32:42.794
Outside of Vegas.

32:42.794 --> 32:45.130
But you better hurry.

32:45.130 --> 32:48.366
They're on the move
in less than an hour.

32:48.366 --> 32:51.336
[tense music]

32:51.336 --> 32:52.637
♪ ♪

32:56.074 --> 32:57.476
- Eyes are in the sky.
Radio on scrambled channel.

32:57.476 --> 32:59.044
Be advised,
license plate camera captured

32:59.044 --> 33:00.645
suspect vehicle heading east

33:00.645 --> 33:02.547
on Wilshire Boulevard
one minute ago.

33:02.547 --> 33:04.316
That's east
on Wilshire Boulevard.

33:04.316 --> 33:06.818
[tense music]

33:06.818 --> 33:09.087
- How come I got
to sit next to nuke?

33:09.087 --> 33:10.956
- It doesn't matter
who sits closest.

33:10.956 --> 33:12.958
Radiation is the same
for all of us.

33:12.958 --> 33:13.959
Minor.

33:13.959 --> 33:16.328
- I still don't like it.

33:16.328 --> 33:20.599
- $10 million payday's gonna
get you past that real quick.

33:20.599 --> 33:22.801
- Can I get mine in crypto?

33:24.202 --> 33:26.838
♪ ♪

33:26.838 --> 33:28.240
- Heads up.

33:28.240 --> 33:29.641
Suspect vehicle spotted west
on Wilshire Boulevard

33:29.641 --> 33:31.142
heading for the freeway.

33:31.142 --> 33:33.645
- 7-Adam-100 two blocks away,
heading northwest on Olive.

33:33.645 --> 33:34.913
What are our rules
of engagement?

33:34.913 --> 33:37.282
- Only one:
don't shoot the nuke.

33:37.282 --> 33:40.285
- 7-Adam-19, five blocks away,
heading south on Figueroa.

33:40.285 --> 33:42.921
- This seems unreal.
Was your first day like this?

33:42.921 --> 33:44.356
- No, I saved my TOs life

33:44.356 --> 33:45.924
after he got shot
during a firefight.

33:45.924 --> 33:47.692
This is a walk in the park.

33:47.692 --> 33:50.128
- All right, 7-Adam-15
on an intercept course.

33:50.128 --> 33:52.664
♪ ♪

33:52.664 --> 33:54.165
- There he is.
- There he is.

33:54.165 --> 33:55.867
[siren wailing]

33:55.867 --> 33:57.969
- We're busted.
Get us the hell out of here.

33:57.969 --> 33:59.871
[engines revving]

33:59.871 --> 34:01.139
Hey, secure that thing!

34:01.139 --> 34:04.142
[energetic tense music]

34:04.142 --> 34:05.877
♪ ♪

34:05.877 --> 34:08.480
- FBI Unit 1,
joining the pursuit.

34:08.480 --> 34:11.049
♪ ♪

34:11.049 --> 34:12.183
- Watch out for that car.

34:12.183 --> 34:13.285
- I see it.

34:13.285 --> 34:14.853
[tires squealing]

34:14.853 --> 34:18.189
♪ ♪

34:18.189 --> 34:20.191
- OK, we're turning here
on Hope Street.

34:20.191 --> 34:21.393
- Go, E, come on!

34:21.393 --> 34:23.128
- 7-Adam-15, two more units

34:23.128 --> 34:25.030
attaching to pursuit
three blocks out.

34:25.030 --> 34:27.999
- Suspect vehicle heading east,
entering Lower Grand.

34:27.999 --> 34:35.006
♪ ♪

34:36.708 --> 34:38.176
- I know we're not supposed
to shoot the device,

34:38.176 --> 34:39.644
but how do you feel about
us crashing into it?

34:39.644 --> 34:41.179
- And I'm the cowboy?

34:41.179 --> 34:43.348
- Well, in theory, it's stable
enough for an outside impact,

34:43.348 --> 34:45.517
but the thing's
60 years old, so--

34:45.517 --> 34:46.918
- Yeah, that--
that sounds like a no.

34:46.918 --> 34:48.520
- Hang on.

34:48.520 --> 34:52.223
♪ ♪

34:52.223 --> 34:57.329
[tires squealing]

34:57.329 --> 34:58.396
- [laughs]

34:58.396 --> 35:01.700
♪ ♪

35:01.700 --> 35:04.369
[engine revving]

35:10.275 --> 35:13.345
[gunfire]

35:13.345 --> 35:14.346
[people screaming]

35:14.346 --> 35:15.547
Bail out!

35:17.382 --> 35:19.451
[gunfire]

35:21.453 --> 35:22.887
[tense music]

35:22.887 --> 35:25.790
[gunfire]

35:25.790 --> 35:27.726
♪ ♪

35:27.726 --> 35:29.427
[bullets ricochet against car]

35:29.427 --> 35:33.565
♪ ♪

35:33.565 --> 35:34.566
- Bring the nuke.

35:34.566 --> 35:36.034
- No way.

35:36.034 --> 35:41.406
♪ ♪

35:41.406 --> 35:42.540
- Three shooters.

35:42.540 --> 35:46.911
♪ ♪

35:46.911 --> 35:48.313
- Cover us.

35:48.313 --> 35:49.314
- Go!

35:49.314 --> 35:52.117
[gunfire]

35:52.117 --> 35:53.251
- Two shooters running off.

35:53.251 --> 35:56.755
♪ ♪

35:56.755 --> 35:58.656
[gunshot]

35:58.656 --> 36:00.458
- Get up!
- Got him, got him.

36:00.458 --> 36:01.526
Shooter down.

36:01.526 --> 36:03.194
♪ ♪

36:03.194 --> 36:04.362
- Penn, slow down!

36:04.362 --> 36:05.997
- Clear the truck.

36:05.997 --> 36:07.432
[tense music]

36:07.432 --> 36:09.734
[people screaming]

36:09.734 --> 36:15.907
♪ ♪

36:15.907 --> 36:17.242
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

36:17.242 --> 36:18.676
- Get down, get down.

36:18.676 --> 36:21.246
[gunfire]

36:21.246 --> 36:23.281
- Go.

36:23.281 --> 36:27.652
♪ ♪

36:27.652 --> 36:28.853
[gunfire]

36:28.853 --> 36:29.988
- Stay down.

36:29.988 --> 36:31.523
- [screams]
- Ridley, pull her in.

36:31.523 --> 36:32.624
I got you cover fire.

36:32.624 --> 36:34.893
[gunfire]

36:34.893 --> 36:39.064
♪ ♪

36:39.064 --> 36:40.298
- Reload.

36:40.298 --> 36:47.305
♪ ♪

36:47.872 --> 36:49.274
[gunfire]

36:49.274 --> 36:50.375
- Why ain't they
shooting at us?

36:50.375 --> 36:51.710
- It's a nuke.

36:51.710 --> 36:53.044
They don't want
to hit the nuke.

36:53.044 --> 36:54.212
[gunfire]

36:54.212 --> 36:56.014
♪ ♪

36:56.014 --> 36:59.117
[gunfire]

36:59.117 --> 37:06.157
♪ ♪

37:06.157 --> 37:08.393
- Officer down.

37:08.393 --> 37:10.095
[gunfire]

37:10.095 --> 37:12.163
Hey, here. Hold on.

37:12.163 --> 37:13.865
♪ ♪

37:13.865 --> 37:15.867
- 7-Adam-15, shots fired.

37:15.867 --> 37:19.070
We have an officer down,
requesting RA at my location.

37:19.070 --> 37:21.539
♪ ♪

37:21.539 --> 37:22.740
- Get up.

37:22.740 --> 37:23.875
Get up!

37:23.875 --> 37:25.343
- The hell you doing?

37:25.343 --> 37:26.411
- Shut up.

37:26.411 --> 37:27.412
- Back off!

37:27.412 --> 37:30.315
Back off
or I'll blow us all up!

37:30.315 --> 37:33.485
You want to be a cowboy?
I will level this place!

37:33.485 --> 37:35.520
[heartbeat pounding]

37:35.520 --> 37:39.424
[muffled shouting]

37:39.424 --> 37:46.464
♪ ♪

37:47.365 --> 37:49.234
[groans]

37:49.234 --> 37:51.169
- On your knees now!

37:51.169 --> 37:53.037
[tense dramatic music]

37:53.037 --> 37:54.839
- [exhales deeply]

37:54.839 --> 37:56.841
[sighs]

37:56.841 --> 37:58.843
♪ ♪

37:58.843 --> 38:01.146
- Nice shot, Officer Nolan.

38:01.146 --> 38:02.413
- Thank you, sir.

38:02.413 --> 38:04.782
Code-4,
all suspects in custody.

38:08.786 --> 38:10.121
- Man, that--

38:10.121 --> 38:12.323
you think tomorrow's
gonna be any quieter?

38:12.323 --> 38:14.859
- Not now that you jinxed it.
- [chuckles]

38:15.827 --> 38:16.961
Ah.

38:16.961 --> 38:18.229
- Looks like you survived
the day, Boot.

38:18.229 --> 38:20.465
- Yeah, sir.
Sergeant, uh, sir.

38:20.465 --> 38:22.066
- Any blemishes?
Don't lie to me.

38:22.066 --> 38:23.134
I will find out.

38:23.134 --> 38:26.571
- Um, no, just a small incident

38:26.571 --> 38:28.473
when Officer Chen and I
found the carjacker OD'ed,

38:28.473 --> 38:30.875
I just puked in the vehicle.

38:30.875 --> 38:32.143
- Dude.

38:32.143 --> 38:33.745
- I wouldn't be so quick
to judge, Officer Penn.

38:33.745 --> 38:34.946
You almost got a blue page

38:34.946 --> 38:36.314
for your reckless behavior
this morning.

38:36.314 --> 38:37.615
- Yes, sir.

38:37.615 --> 38:39.117
I truly appreciate
your leniency.

38:39.117 --> 38:40.585
- Don't mistake it
for kindness.

38:40.585 --> 38:42.287
You remain on very thin ice.

38:42.287 --> 38:44.355
- Yes, sir.
See you tomorrow.

38:44.355 --> 38:46.758
- Unfortunately.
Try to suck less.

38:46.758 --> 38:48.026
- Will do.

38:49.527 --> 38:52.530
[upbeat music]

38:52.530 --> 38:54.032
♪ ♪

38:54.032 --> 38:55.600
- How's lieutenant life
treating you?

38:55.600 --> 38:56.968
- I love the pay bump.

38:56.968 --> 38:58.770
Just wish it came
under better circumstances.

38:58.770 --> 38:59.938
- What do you mean?

38:59.938 --> 39:03.208
- I just can't help
but to feel guilty

39:03.208 --> 39:04.375
because I got rewarded

39:04.375 --> 39:06.044
for exposing
the corruption scandal.

39:06.044 --> 39:07.178
Lot of cops got fired.

39:07.178 --> 39:09.180
- Yeah, well, they deserved it.

39:09.180 --> 39:10.281
So you deserve this promotion

39:10.281 --> 39:12.550
no matter how it came about,
OK?

39:12.550 --> 39:14.452
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

39:14.452 --> 39:16.154
- Just doesn't seem right.

39:16.154 --> 39:17.455
We saved the city,

39:17.455 --> 39:19.691
and our reward is sitting
in rush hour traffic.

39:19.691 --> 39:22.627
- Got to love LA.

39:22.627 --> 39:25.630
- ♪ Even I feel like
there's nothing ♪

39:25.630 --> 39:28.032
- Hey.

39:28.032 --> 39:30.168
Heard your guy
puked all over a crime scene.

39:30.168 --> 39:32.503
- Well, at least he didn't
light his duty manual on fire

39:32.503 --> 39:33.605
and throw it out the window.

39:33.605 --> 39:35.540
Shoot out the tires?

39:35.540 --> 39:38.276
- He's a little rough around
the edges, but it's day one.

39:38.276 --> 39:39.277
I'll get him under control.

39:39.277 --> 39:40.612
- Likewise.

39:40.612 --> 39:43.681
So wait,
since they both screwed up--

39:43.681 --> 39:46.884
- Uh, yeah,
I guess it's a draw.

39:46.884 --> 39:48.419
- Tomorrow's a new day.

39:48.419 --> 39:50.355
- Yes, it is.

39:50.355 --> 39:51.589
- Mm-hmm.

39:51.589 --> 39:53.858
[soft upbeat music]

39:53.858 --> 39:56.828
Well, I will see you tomorrow.

39:56.828 --> 39:58.930
- Look forward to it.

39:58.930 --> 40:00.565
- Good night.

40:00.565 --> 40:04.702
- ♪ And the blossoms will die
and hit the tarmac ♪

40:04.702 --> 40:10.041
♪ And the fruit will
grow eager to justify that ♪

40:10.041 --> 40:14.812
♪ And I love this, I do,
but it don't mean a thing ♪

40:14.812 --> 40:16.648
♪ Till I have you right here
next to me ♪

40:16.648 --> 40:17.982
- What?

40:17.982 --> 40:20.218
- Oh, it's nothing.

40:20.218 --> 40:22.320
- If you want to fool around,
just ask.

40:22.320 --> 40:23.321
- No.

40:23.321 --> 40:26.991
I mean, of course I do.

40:26.991 --> 40:28.126
It's just--

40:28.126 --> 40:31.195
- It's just what?

40:31.195 --> 40:34.232
- You're happy, right?

40:34.232 --> 40:36.134
- In this moment, I'm sleepy

40:36.134 --> 40:38.936
and a little concerned about
whatever this conversation is.

40:38.936 --> 40:43.474
But in general, yes,
I'm very happy.

40:43.474 --> 40:45.043
- OK, good.

40:45.043 --> 40:48.880
- ♪ You wear make-up
for all your phone calls ♪

40:48.880 --> 40:51.316
- So do you want to
fool around or not?

40:51.316 --> 40:53.351
- I mean, if you're offering.

40:53.351 --> 40:55.920
- ♪ When they say
life is too short ♪

40:55.920 --> 40:57.021
[smooching]

40:57.021 --> 40:59.524
♪ They're not stuck in yours ♪

40:59.524 --> 41:01.926
♪ ♪

41:01.926 --> 41:06.097
♪ If your world was
drained like a well ♪

41:06.097 --> 41:08.399
♪ Reduced to its shell ♪

41:08.399 --> 41:12.970
♪ Your lipsticks will
still smell like before ♪

41:12.970 --> 41:16.541
♪ And summer still comes ♪

41:16.541 --> 41:18.176
♪ ♪

41:18.176 --> 41:23.581
♪ Summer still comes ♪

41:23.581 --> 41:27.552
♪ Summer still comes ♪

41:27.552 --> 41:29.721
♪ ♪

41:29.721 --> 41:35.093
♪ And the grass will go brown
and yellow and gold ♪

41:35.093 --> 41:40.431
♪ And the dust will set
laughter in faces and folds ♪

41:40.431 --> 41:44.068
♪ And I love this, I do,
but it don't mean a thing ♪

41:44.068 --> 41:46.037
- Hey, it's me.

41:46.037 --> 41:49.107
It's like 5:00 in the morning
where you are,

41:49.107 --> 41:51.642
so I'm glad you didn't pick up.

41:51.642 --> 41:55.113
Uh, miss you.
[chuckles]

41:55.113 --> 41:56.247
Hard day.

41:56.247 --> 41:58.149
Would have been nice
to snuggle up,

41:58.149 --> 42:01.452
have you tell me
I did a good job.

42:01.452 --> 42:04.288
Anyway, just got home.

42:04.288 --> 42:07.625
Hope you're having a good time
being a soldier.

42:07.625 --> 42:09.527
I love you.

42:09.527 --> 42:12.530
[soft upbeat music]

42:12.530 --> 42:13.965
[sighs]

42:13.965 --> 42:17.135
♪ ♪

42:17.135 --> 42:19.670
You did a good job today.

42:21.773 --> 42:23.107
Yeah, that was weird.

42:25.510 --> 42:28.513
[upbeat music]

42:28.513 --> 42:35.553
♪ ♪

42:58.476 --> 42:59.510
- Damn it.
